{"http://www.concordia.ca/artsci/biology/events/cuevents/artsci/philosophy/2016/12/15/PHILDefenceRamusovic.html": [["http://www.concordia.ca/content/shared/en/events/artsci/philosophy/2016/12/15/PHILDefenceRamusovic.html", " is completing his MA in Philosophy at Concordia.", "This paper clarifies Hegel\u2019s argument within the \u201cComedy\u201d section of the ", "by fleshing out and developing Hegel\u2019s basic point concerning the individual and its clash with abstract universals. It does this by engaging current scholarship on \u201cComedy,\u201d building upon some of its fundamentals, yet showing that the picture we get of \u201cComedy\u201d in this literature should be supplemented. To this end, the paper explicates Hegel\u2019s claim that the individual is a \u201cnegative power,\u201d and then develops a central point in Hegel\u2019s section on \u201cComedy,\u201d namely, that in comedy abstract universals are put in play and revealed as they are actually made concrete in the lives of individuals. This reveals the pretensions of abstract universals, unmasking the gap between what we might think of a universal, such as honesty, and this universal in it concrete/actual form. It this pretense and gap that Hegel finds comedic.", "\u00a9 Concordia University"], ["Facebook", "Twitter", "LinkedIn", "GooglePlus", "Calendar", "Submit an event", "Latest news", "Back to top", "Concordia University", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada"], ["Facebook", "Twitter", "LinkedIn", "GooglePlus", "Calendar", "Submit an event", "Latest news", "Back to top", "Concordia University", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada", "Montreal", "Quebec", "Canada"], ["Calendar - Graduate", "Calendar - Undergraduate", "Class schedules", "Class cancellations", "Course registration", "Important academic dates", "More academic resources", "Concordia st